    "Context Rendering GAN (CRGAN) (Chen et al. 2019) have been proposed for a similar task, but in this case, the images are translated from a source data set to a target one.",
    "Individual-preserving and environmental-switching cyclic generation network (IPES-GAN) generates new images by cropping a human body and adding it to a target background image, while preserving the pedestrian's identity and pose.",
    "Also in face recognition, GAN-based approaches are mainly used for data augmentation.",
    "In particular, in Mokhayeri et al. (2020) the augmentation process focuses on face pose.",
    "The source (real) images are transformed into a 3D image using a 3D model to simulate a specific pose."
